revision.text:
The '''''Almanach de Bruxelles''''' is a now defunct [[France|French]] social register that listed [[royal family|royal]] and [[nobility|noble]] [[dynasties]] of [[Europe]]. It was established in 1918 during the [[Second World War]] to compete against the prominent German [[Almanach de Gotha]].<ref>March 17, 1918. [https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1918/03/17/109329982.pdf Almanach de Gotha has a french rival] at ''[[New York Times]]''</ref>
==See also== * ''[[Almanach de Gotha]]''
